The '''Nimboran''' languages are a small independent [[language family|family]] of [[Papuan languages]] in the classification of [[Malcolm Ross (linguist)|Malcolm Ross]], that had been part of [[Stephen Wurm]]'s [[Trans–New Guinea languages|Trans–New Guinea]] proposal. However, when proto-Nimboran pronouns are reconstructed ''(*genam'' "I" and ''kom'' or ''komot'' "thou"), they have little resemblance to the proto-TNG pronouns ''*na'' and ''*ga.'' Usher places them in a [[North Papuan languages|North Papuan]] stock that resembles Cowan's proposal.<ref>[https://sites.google.com/site/newguineaworld/families/north-new-guinea/west-north-new-guinea/grime-river]</ref>
==Classification== * '''Nimboran''' family: [[Kemtuik language|Kemtuik]]–[[Gresi language|Gresi]], [[Mlap language|Mlap]], [[Mekwei language|Mekwei]], [[Nimboran language|Nimboran]]
==Pronouns== The pronouns Ross reconstructs for proto-Nimboran are,
:{| class=wikitable |- | '''I''' || ''*genam'' |- | '''thou''' || ''*kom, komot'' |- | '''s/he''' || ? |}
